subSubSection.paragraph:
Bradyetes
cf. 
inermis

morphotypes 1–3 differ in the combination of the following characters (
Figs 3–4
): morphotype 1 (
Fig. 4
), body length 2.60–3.00 mm, is characterized by 1) a sausage-like spermatheca that has nearly the same width proximally and distally, 2) a maxillule praecoxal arthrite with 11 setae: 8 long plus 1 short terminal setae (marked by a star in 
Fig. 4
), 1 anterior and 1 posterior setae (this short terminal seta is absent in morphotypes 2 and 3), and 3) a P1 with a well-developed lateral lobe on the endopod and a plumose basal medial seta (this lobe is poorly developed or absent and the medial seta is nude in morphotypes 2 and 3). Morphotype 1 shares with morphotype 2 the maxillular epipodite which is equipped with 8 setae (6–7 setae are present in morphotype 3).
